<H1 class="h1" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">Europe, Middle East and Africa - Financial Advisor Role</H1>

<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
The Financial Advisor role in EMEA focuses on ultra-high-net-worth clients with more than US $1 million in investable assets.  In addition to financial knowledge and technical skills, Financial Advisors must be able to nurture genuine relationships with their clients, understand their hopes and dreams and develop a holistic grasp of what they want and need.
</p>

<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
A Financial Advisor at Merrill Lynch Wealth Management
</p>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Is an experienced private banker</li>
	<li>Has an established book of business</li>
	<li>Is independent, exhibits integrity, initiative, strong motivation and attention to detail</li>
	<li>Is fluent in English and the language of the prospective client market</li>
	<li>Has good presentation and communication skills and is a good listener</li>
	<li>Demonstrates an appropriate level of technical and professional skills and knowledge</li>
	<li>Recognizes and values individual uniqueness and differences; demonstrates client focus, respect for the individual, teamwork and responsible citizenship</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>What the Role Offers</b></H2>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
Our Financial Advisors in EMEA have access to a comprehensive array of products and services to meet clients&#39; needs and a range of tools and support to assist them in executing their roles.
</p>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Tools and processes</b></H2>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>An approach to wealth management that includes advisory, discretionary and wealth structuring methods to align with clients&#39; needs</li>
	<li>A wealth management process and financial modeling tools</li>
	<li>Open architecture access to best-in-class products</li>
	<li>Facility to book assets on either the Merrill Lynch Wealth Management international or Swiss platform</li>
	<li>Access to institutional resources and capital markets</li>
	<li>Support from senior management and wealth management specialists</li>
	<li>Global and local expertise</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Products and services</b></H2>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Innovative and broad product platform that responds to current opportunities through our specialist networks</li>
	<li>More than 470 non-US mutual funds from approximately 60 asset management companies domiciled in jurisdictions including Luxembourg, Dublin and the Cayman Islands</li>
	<li>Extensive hedge fund and private equity offerings and structured product capabilities</li>
	<li>Top-ranked independent research with actionable ideas and products</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>How to Apply</b></H2>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
To apply for the Financial Advisor role in the Europe, Middle East &amp; Africa region, you need to
</p>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Send an email message to <a href="mailto: emea_fa_recruitment@ml.com" class="p">emea_fa_recruitment@ml.com</a></li>
	<li>Attach your CV or resume</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
Your application will be reviewed, and you will be contacted if there is an interest in your qualifications.
</p>

